Saraswatichandra is an upcoming Indian soap opera which will start airing on Star Plus from February 25, 2013. It will air every Mon-Fri at 7:30 pm. The story will be based on the famous Gujarati novel Saraswatichandra written by Govardhanram Madhavram Tripathi. Protagonists of the show are Gautam Rode and Jennifer Winget. 
On February 14, 2013, exclusive premiere trailer of the show was aired as a Valentine's Day special on Star Plus facebook page.
Replacement.
"Saraswatichandra" will replace the show Mujhse Kuchh Kehti...Yeh Khamoshiyaan, due to low TRP ratings after the show's main actor's exit.
